repo.description: Parse and serialize minecraft packets, plus authentication and encryption.

body:
Now that ES6 is gaining more widespread adoption, including in Node and modern browsers, this PR attempts to use in node-minecraft-protocol natively, instead of through gulp/babel.

Requires enabling experimental in-progress V8 flags, so this is probably premature, but might be worth doing at some point (unless we want to always use newer ES features through babel, e.g., ES7 when ES6 is well-supported, then ES8 when ES7, etc.).

Node.js ES6 documentation: https://nodejs.org/en/docs/es6/

commit.message:
Use supported ES6 destructuring statement

Although it is legal ES6 syntax, Node v5.3.0 even with
--harmony_destructuring (marked as "in progress") fails at:

src/transforms/framing.js:42
      ({ value, size, error } = readVarInt(this.buffer, offset) || { error: "Not enough data" });
       ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^

ReferenceError: Invalid left-hand side in assignment
    at exports.runInThisContext (vm.js:53:16)
    at Module._compile (module.js:374:25)
    at Object.Module._extensions..js (module.js:405:10)
    at Module.load (module.js:344:32)
    at Function.Module._load (module.js:301:12)
    at Module.require (module.js:354:17)
    at require (internal/module.js:12:17)
    at Object.<anonymous> (/Users/admin/games/voxeljs/node-minecraft-protocol/src/client.js:6:15)
    at Module._compile (module.js:398:26)
    at Object.Module._extensions..js (module.js:405:10)

The `let { value, size, error } = ` form works, use it instead here.

Add V8 flags for node ES6 in-progress destructuring, default parameters

These features are currently (tested on node v5.4.1) marked as "in
progress" in V8 and not enabled by default, or with --es_staging (aka
--harmony), so enable them explicitly. See https://nodejs.org/en/docs/es6/
Remove ES6 default parameters, not enabled in Node v5.4.1
Remove ES6 destructuring, not enabled in Node v5.4.1
